  "fullText": "Parameters Task Creation Rule Priority Task Type Shipments/Batch = 2 Pallet Pick, Task Type = PP PP Strict Load Sequence Trailer % = 70% Cart Pick Pallet, Task Type = CP CP Previous Max Tax Priority = 60 Step 1 - Determine which Tasks are eligible for Batching vs strict locad sequence Step 2 - Update Task Priorities for Strict Load Sequence tasks sequenced by:\n1. Load Sequence (ext_sys_shipment_id)\n2. Task Rule ID (adheres to Task Creation Rule Priority and assumed Task Type)\n3. Task ID (adheres to sequencing defined in Task Creation) Shipment 1 (ext_sys_shipment_id = 0101) Task Number Priority (Pallet Pick rule 1st) Priority (Cart Pick rule 2nd) Shipment 2 (ext_sys_shipment_id = 0102) Shipment 3 (ext_sys_shipment_id = 0103) Shipment 4 (ext_sys_shipment_id = 0104) Batched across Shipment Step 1 - Determine which Pallets are eligible for Batching vs strict locad sequence Step 3 - Establish Batches by:\n1. Shipments/Batch\n2. Trailer %\n3. Sequenced by ext_sys_shipment_id\n4. Loop executed by Task Rule ID\n\nResults below for Loop 1 (Cart Pick) Step 4 - Sequence within each Batch by:\n1. Task Batch Number (from Step 2)\n2. Pallet sequence within the Shipment\nResetting the counter for each Batch within the Shipment Step 5 - Update Task Priorities sequenced by:\n1. Accounting for \"Previous Max Tax Priority\"\n2. Task Batch Number (from Step 3)\n3. Shipment-Batch Sequence\n4. Inner-loop executed by Task Batch Number\n\nResults below for Loop 1.1 (Batch 1 - Cart Pick) Step 5 - Update Task Priorities sequenced by:\n1. Accounting for \"Previous Max Tax Priority\"\n2. Task Batch Number (from Step 3)\n3. Shipment-Batch Sequence\n4. Inner-loop executed by Task Batch Number\n\nResults below for Loop 1.2 (Batch 2 - Cart Pick) Step 5 - Update Task Priorities sequenced by:\n1. Accounting for \"Previous Max Tax Priority\"\n2. Task Batch Number (from Step 3)\n3. Shipment-Batch Sequence\n4. Inner-loop executed by Task Batch Number\n\nResults below for Loop 1.3 (Ba